runs.comm: run down to third man
short and down the leg side, no question that's a wide
wide and slashed over slip, deliberate shot, well placed
short of a length, Gilchrist forced back to defend
leg-side wide again. Flintoff not pitching anything up but struggling for his line
lovely ball, beats Gilchrist's inside edge as he aims a fairly nothing drive off the back foot
angled to Pietersen at backward point and he tries a pointless hurl at the stumps
backfoot block, sliding stop by Bell in the covers
two steps down the track and blasted over long-on ... it trickles over the rope but a lovely strike
squirted to point where Pietersen fields
savage straight drive, Anderson faced with being a hero or ducking, opts to live to bowl another ball
and another slash over the covers, Joyce sprints round from third man on the rope
fuller, lovely drive through extra cover
half volley, cracked straight at Ian Bell at cover
Gilchrist looks to swing to leg, thin inside edge into his pads and the field converges
slower ball, almost a yorker, and Gilchrist can do no more than prod it into the covers
slashed to cover where Pietersen makes a total hash of stopping it and gives two where there were none
attempted pull but Gilchrist misses
full toss, Gilchrist smacks it right back at Flintoff who fields in his follow through
attempted yorker, Gilchrist chops down on it and it pootles up to mid-off
MAXIMUM! half volley, swished over square leg
Hayden onto the front foot as everything Anderson has bowled so far has been pitched up, but this one isn't and his slash comes off the splice and loops to Dalrymple at mid-off
big slash and well taken by Nixon
run off the face of the bat as if he was giving slip-catching practice, super shot&
tip and run to Joyce at point, good communication
more tip and run to Pietersen in the covers ... he was a bit slow onto that and his shy at the stumps missed anyway
shortish, onto the back foot, patted into the covers and great running even though it was right to the inrushing fielder
chopped down to third man
just short and Ponting onto it like a big cat and smacked into the first tier of the stand at square leg
smacked to the other side, slashed over backward point
driven in the air over the covers - he opened the face there - and although Pietersen just caught it inside the ropes, they ran four anyhow

high high - very high - and Lewis at mid-on waited an age and made a complete hash of it. It was right down his throat and he seemed far too casual, it bounced out of his hands and he couldn't grab the rebound. Numpty, as Mr Miller loves to say
pulled over deep midwicket ... carnage
in the slot, lofted drive over mid-off which lands a foot over the rope
and again ...smashed over deep midwicket and dropped in the crowd
driven to mid-off and a quick single ... what an anticlimax
punched to mid-on. Anderson laughs
smashed to mid-off where Dalrymple makes a good sprawling stop
Gilchrist back and blocks
and he does ... lofted in between the in and out field on the off
pushed to point where Dalrymple overruns the ball but recovers quickly to prevent the second
roundarm delivery, Gilchrist aims a reverse sweep but misses
drive straight and high and Peter Parker signals a six ... and his oh-so-tight shirt is stretched to the limit
punched to long-on
nurdled round the corner and with Panesar on his knees as he fields, a second is easy
in the air but short of the incoming deep midwicket
Oh yes! Gilchrist onto one knee and he smashes the ball over deep midwicket and it ends up halfway up the Bill O'Reilly stand
punched to deep mid-off
Ponting back and straight to point
heaved inches over the man at midwicket, the kind of shot Ponting wouldn't normally play even in the nets, but anything goes in Twenty20
Gilchrist shapes to pepper the Bill O'Reilly stand again but gets an inside edge into his off stump
reverse sweep, Anderson dives but only pushes the ball over the rope  - and just laughs
blocked, Nixon scurries out to field
full, swished to deep square leg and good running to create a second
another reverse sweep, Hussey stretches to make it into a full toss, Anderson fields properly this time
Ponting waits, leans back and smacks it in the air over the covers to the sweeper
swept straight to the man short on the 45
sliced drive over the covers
hit hard through extra cover, timed and placed
Hussey moves outside leg stump, Dalrymple follows him and also does him in the air, a big swish and miss
tossed up again, swept single to the man on the 45
checked drive, no follow through at all, and it still has enough legs to go over the head of long-off
hello, massive! Hussey down the track and whacks that over the long midwicket boundary - that's huge
Hussey comes right down the track looking for the same shot this time - the crack over midwicket - and his stumps are taken by Nixon, with some sharp work
drops that short, wide, and Symonds lobs that lazily over extra cover. Dalrymple wings it back in and there's a chance of a run-out, but Panesar throws to the wrong end
dibbled out behind square
flighted up there and that's driven to mid-on
pushed up there again and an easy drive to mid-on once more
loosener, straying sown leg and that's flicked up down the leg-side, too fine for Pietersen who gives chase in vain
on the spot, good delivery and that's driven towards mid-on - midwicket came round and dived on it to stop it
good start, pushed off the legs to a wide long-on
sounded like he'd got hold of that, but in fact he didn't quite time it and that is bunted out to midwicket where it bounces in acres of space
Collingwood goes wider, and the batsman tries to cut that but only manages to get the toe-end of the bat on it
pushed right up there and Symonds does well to dig that out towards cover
flighted up there and that's well driven out to the cover boundary
boosted over mid-on and it's dropped in the crowd
wide and Symonds flat bats that forward to mid-off
waits for that one and works it cleverly round with just a dink behind square
good length delivery and that's worked out to long-on where it's cannoned back in quickly
pushed up there and that's defended
down on one knee and tries to flick that high over square leg where Lewis makes no mistake this time, having dropped him on 16. Lewis shows the ball to the crowd... because he can
straight and shortish, Symonds waits on it and does well to late cut that very finely indeed before setting off quickly for a run
defended first up
driven out to Pietersen out at a very wide long-on
driven into his toes. Ouch
worked off the back foot behind point and that's a relatively good over for England
guided behind point off the back foot and that's good running from Australia
short, just outside off and that's some sharp work in close from Collingwood, winged right back in over the stumps and Nixon who does the rest. Mix up of the yes, no, wait, sorry variety
wide down the leg side and there's an appeal for a strangle, but it clearly flicked the outside of the pad
defended on the front foot
dabbed down off the back foot down to third man
attempted yorker worked out to the man at long-on
slower ball, wide and clattered with a one-bounce four through extra cover, driving right through that one
low full toss, worked off the legs through square with a bottom-hand flick and that goes all the way - strength and placement
pushed up there and Symonds rushes that out to mid-on
slower ball again, off cutter, worked to gully and Vaughan wings that back in underarm while diving
attempted yorker and they push hard, looking for two, but it's not on
wide, full and that's worked in front of point off the back foot
short and tries to hook that through midwicket, doesn't get hold of it, though
whack! Lovely shot in front of midwicket and that's just inches over the boundary
tries to hook that one as well, but the ricochet goes in front of gully to Vaughan
straight, but Symonds stands tall and walks back, making room to send that up and over through point
huge! That's a flat bat swipe right over mid-on
gives himself room to cut that down the ground for one
low full toss, worked out down the ground to Pietersen on the long-on boundary
slower delivery and he tries to heave that one over to midwicket, mis-times it and Nixon trotting into the leg-side to field it
yorker, worked out to midwicket and it's thrown back in on the bounce
slower ball, strays down leg and Symonds can only get a leg on it as it goes to the man up at fine leg

clattered over midwicket and Dalrymple has a one-handed attempt to leap up and get that but it goes over him and just clears the rope. He was two yards in, if he'd have been on the ropes he'd have had that. As it is, that's the 12th six, equalling the record in a Twenty20 international
dot ball at 85mph (137 kmh) as Symonds plays under that one, trying to cut it
tries the yorker, but there's a touch of width and that's cut off the back foot behind point
rocketed through extra cover off the back foot and that's smashed away, scorcher
yorker, driven off the back foot to cover and that brings up the 200
short and sharp and that pings off the glove into the grille. Ouch. "Well bowled Andrew Flintoff" announces Nasser Hussain. Flintoff checks if White is OK
worked to long-on and that's some great running from the pair
yorker, good start but fluffs the chance to run out Symonds at his end
huge, huger, hugest! That goes big over midwicket and it's fluffed in the crowd
Pietersen carbon-copies Lewis's drop earlier when Ponting was on 16 out at long-on. KP grins at the crowd, sheepishly
that's into the Ladies Stand there, over long-on, and that extends the sixes record
dropped into space at deep midwicket
worked to square and Anderson has the worst analysis of any bowler in Twenty20 internationals (1 for 64 from his four overs)
